issue.title: update the WWDRCA certificate recommendation
issue.body:
Currently the plugin recommends downloading `https://apple.com/certificationauthority/AppleWWDRCA.cer`, which is set to expire on Feb. 7, 2023, 9:48 p.m. (only 4ish months from now). 

This updates the recommendation to download `https://apple.com/certificationauthority/AppleWWDRCAG4.cer`, which replaced this certificate (per https://developer.apple.com/news/?id=5zb13auf). 

This PR does **_not_** include code to check whether the Apple WWDRCA has expired, nor that it is set to expire soon. It simply updates the translations.

pull_request.title: Merge consecutive identical lines on receipt
pull_request.body:
Customers rightfully complain that buying 30 tickets uses up a lot of receipt paper when it does not need to.

In pretixPOS, we have good reasons for not merging receipt lines since they can individually be interacted with, therefore I propose to merge really only upon printing. I was struggling whether to put this logic into POS or PRINT, but I think it's okay to put it here.

issue.title: Django signal instrumentation breaks receiver signatures

milestone.title: Django update
milestone.description: Collections of improvements to our Django integration.

issue.body:
### How do you use Sentry?

Sentry Saas (sentry.io)

### Version

1.9.9

### Steps to Reproduce

I have my own instrumentation around django signals which was broken by the changes in pull request #1526. (commit 412f824b8b53c444671c81ec8e119eba66308064)

My code wraps the django signal class, and makes use of the `receiver.__name__`. As of sentry version 1.9.9, I receive the wrapper name, rather than the expected receiver method name. 

My code (simplified):
```
class TimedSignal(Signal):
    """ Same as signal, but we report on any slow functions """
    def send(self, sender, **named):
        for receiver in self._live_receivers(sender):
            print("receiver.__qualname__ =", receiver.__qualname__)
            print("receiver.__name__ =", receiver.__name__)
            ... (logic with these values) ...
```

Suggested fix:
The `wrapper` method defined within `sentry_receiver_wrapper` should use builtin [functools.wraps](https://docs.python.org/3/library/functools.html#functools.wraps), to maintain the signature of the original method. 

For example:
```
from functools import wraps
...
        def sentry_receiver_wrapper(receiver):
            # type: (Callable[..., Any]) -> Callable[..., Any]
            @wraps(receiver)
            def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):
```


### Expected Result

I expect to see information about the original receiver method, for example:
```
receiver.__qualname__ = fetch_driver_change_data
receiver.__name__ = fetch_driver_change_data
```


### Actual Result

Instead, I get information about the sentry wrapper:
```
receiver.__qualname__ = patch_signals.<locals>._sentry_live_receivers.<locals>.sentry_receiver_wrapper.<locals>.wrapper
receiver.__name__ = wrapper
```

comment.body: This also just broke our system and I'Ve verified that the suggested fix above works

issue.title: participant name of subscription is None, can't buy ticket
issue.body:
### Problem and impact

I created a shop with a "non-entry" product granting a subscription to a customer. When buying this subscription product, the user did not provide a participation name. Therefore no participant name was saved to to the subscription.

When trying to use the subscription to buy an entry-product in another shop, a participant name is required, but the fields are disabled (as the subscription is configured to me non-transferable). I cannot proceed with checkout at this point.

### Expected behaviour

I expect pretix to force customers to provide a participant name when the subscription is bought (for non-transferable subscriptions). Maybe

* show the participant name question for products granting a non-transferable subscription even when it's not configured otherwise
* force subscription-granting products to be an entry-product? even though that doesn't guarantee the name question being shown right? it can still be disabled
* allow to set a name when using the subscription for the first time if the stored name ist None (if you want to allow the name to be None)

### Steps to reproduce

1. create an organizer with a subscription type (non-transferable)
2. create a "shop" where customers can buy the subscription. Default settings, make the product non-entry.
3. buy a subscription through that shop. There should be no participant name question.
4. Create a second event where customers can buy an entry ticket that requires the subscription.
5. Try to buy a ticket to the event with the subscription. See screenshots on the problem there.

### Screenshots

![Screenshot from 2022-10-23 17-46-17](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5970076/197403044-cb90c4d4-9389-4452-bfe7-319845b27861.png)

The fields are disabled, empty, and required.

![Screenshot from 2022-10-23 17-47-30](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5970076/197403126-8f9e67b3-4e1f-4d54-a7a5-344aef6cf9d1.png)

The subscriptions stored name is `None`.


### Link

_No response_

### Browser (software, desktop or mobile?) and version

_No response_

### Operating system, dependency versions

_No response_

### Version

b4a73696423566d3793948fec1c78a480136800e

comment.body:
> I expect pretix to force customers to provide a participant name when the subscription is bought (for non-transferable subscriptions).

It's unfortunately not that simple: If the membership is *used* for a non-admission product, there would not be a problem. It's therefore possible to have non-transferable memberships on non-admission products in some situations.

Asking the user for the name on first usage would be a solution. The most simple "solution" would be to issue a **warning** in the backend if the case is likely to occur with a given configuration

pull_request.title: Stripe Connect: Fix account name retrieval
pull_request.body:
I faced today an issue that I was not able to properly connect my test Stripe account using our staging keys: The connect account name was empty.

According to the Stripe API docs, with 2019-02-19 some fields got shuffled around - so according to this, we're lucky this didn't break yet in our faces: https://stripe.com/docs/api/accounts/object

Interestingly enough, even with the new, updated hashed, my API-calls do net yield a `business_profile` or `email`...
